Troubleshooting Tips
OpenVAS Issues:

If gvm-setup fails, check disk space (requires 5GB+)
Verify all services running: sudo systemctl status gvmd gsad ospd-openvas
Reset admin password: sudo gvmd --user=admin --new-password=NewPass123
ELK Stack Issues:

Elasticsearch won't start: Check Java installation and memory (requires 2GB+ RAM)
Logstash not processing: Verify file path in configuration matches actual location
Kibana connection error: Ensure Elasticsearch is running on port 9200
Python Script Issues:

Import errors: Verify virtual environment is activated
XML parsing fails: Check XML file is valid and complete
Empty DataFrames: Verify XML structure matches parser expectations
Conclusion
This lab provided hands-on experience with enterprise vulnerability management workflows. Students learned to deploy OpenVAS for asset discovery, develop custom risk scoring algorithms, and visualize security data using the ELK Stack. These skills are essential for security analysts, penetration testers, and IT security professionals responsible for vulnerability management programs.

Key takeaways include understanding CVSS scoring, automating vulnerability analysis with Python, and creating actionable security dashboards. The risk scoring methodology demonstrated can be adapted to organizational needs by adjusting multipliers and criticality factors.

Continue practicing by scanning different network ranges, refining scoring algorithms, and creating custom Kibana visualizations to meet specific reporting requirements.
